Currently there is no way to tell approximately how many matches there will be for a query without executing it and counting the results.  This is very slow and inefficent.  It would be great if a new service were added to count the number of results that will be returned from a filter.  Being able to perform the action on more than one filter at a time would also be really nice.  In my case, i am displaying a list of all of the named queries and their counts.

I was expecting something like:

{code}
public long countIssues(User user, String filterId) throws RemoteException
    {
        SearchRequest loadedSR = ManagerFactory.getSearchRequestManager().getRequest(user, new Long(filterId));

        if (loadedSR == null)
        {
            throw new RemoteValidationException("Could not getRequest a search with this id: " + filterId);
        }

        try
        {
            searchProvider.searchCount(loadedSR, user)
        }
        catch (SearchException e)
        {
            throw new RemoteException("Error occurred during searching", e);
        }
    }
{code}
